Vice President Joe Biden met with Cypriot President Nicos Anastasiades to discuss strengthening the strategic partnership between the United States and Cyprus. They welcomed the appointment of UN Special Advisor Espen Barth Eide as an opportunity to energize the settlement talks in line with the Joint Declaration of February 11, 2014. The leaders also discussed Cyprus' potential contributions to the region's energy security and agreed that unifying the island as a bizonal, bicommunal federation would benefit all Cypriots.